<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-01-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-01-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="667" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d667">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Toomey</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington
                                        D. C.</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-01-09"><hi rend="italic">January 9,
                                1900</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p rend="flushleft"><hi rend="smallcaps">Pennsylvania Milling and Export
                                Co.</hi>:</p>
                        <p>Ambassador Choate telegraphs to-day inquiring if your flour was sold for
                            future delivery; also how does your present interest appear?</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">John Hay.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>